description:
My place is located in South Harlem (SOHA) walking distance to central park west. My place is good for couples, solo adventurers, and business travelers or locals who just need a quick place to stay for a night or 2 . Location is perfect, close to the best restaurants in Harlem and night life has the right amount of vibe.

The best thing about my place is the open space and privacy that it comes with. The cozy feel will make you never wanna go out .

I have cable and all the basic amenities that you'll need.  I trust your common sense to know what you can use or not. For instance ( you  should already know that you cant use my clothes  :) )

Usually I rent my place when I'm on a business trip or away on vacation. However, if assistance is needed, I can coordinate with my guests to send someone to help.

The apartment is located on120th/8th AVE . Prime neighborhood in Harlem , south of 125th street, close to ABCD line on 116th and 125th street stops , coffee shops , restaurants and more. Safe area  for clean, responsible, single and like minded individuals.

Prime neighborhood in Harlem,  You wont need to take the subway since you can walk to everything but if you must , you are 2 minutes walking distance to ABCD line on 116th and 125th street stops . Street parking also are pretty easy . I get around with ZIP Car and there a couple close by. The closest is right on 118th and 8th ave.

The only requirement I have is cleaning.  A clean place is a must for me . Please leave the place as you found it before check out.

hosts.about:
I'm creative , cool, calm, collected, cultured and classic. 5 things I cant live without are: my passport, my  phone , my dunkin coffee , my sunglasses  and my black boots. My favorite travel destinations are: London, Paris, anywhere in the Caribbean and the whole continent of Africa. My favorite reads have been thus far "The art of war and Passion Marks". I'm a writer so it can be difficult for me to agree with one's point of view but I can certainly respect it. For movies, I like anything scary and anything written by Shonda Rhimes. I listen to music for inspiration so anything lyrically stimulating usually does it for me. I'm not really picky when it comes to food , so long as there's chicken involved, I'm good. 

Having me as a guest or host is a privilege . I'm pretty mellow and clean, I'm a minimalist , therefore I don't do clutter. I'm open minded and free spirited but at the same time I have ground rules and reserve the right to express a different opinion. I travel a lot so I have seen and experienced a lot of different culture, which makes me easy to get along with. I'm culturally grounded and image driven, therefore manners and class are very important to me.  My motto in life is to never get too comfortable... 
Respect is universal  and common sense is definitely pun intended.
